'''Ali El Abdi''' ({{langx|ar|عَلِيّ الْعَابِدِيّ}}; born 20 December 1993), known as '''Ali Abdi''', is a Tunisian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] for {{French football updater|Nice}} club [[OGC Nice|Nice]] and the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]].

==Club career==
Abdi made his professional debut with [[JS Kairouan]] in a 0–0 [[Tunisian Ligue Professionnelle 1]] tie with [[EGS Gafsa]] on 25 December 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2011/12/25/tunisia/ligue-1/js-kairouanaise/el-gawafel-sportives-de-gafsa/1219492/|title=Kairouan vs. EGS Gafsa - 25 December 2011 - Soccerway|website=Soccerway}}</ref> On 24 June 2019, Abdi moved to [[Paris FC]] in the French [[Ligue 2]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-ali-abdi-club-africain-au-paris-fc/1033461|title=Transferts : Ali Abdi (Club Africain) au Paris FC - Foot - Transferts|website=L'Équipe}}</ref>

On 21 July 2021, he signed a two-year contract with [[Stade Malherbe Caen|Caen]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Stade Malherbe Caen|Caen]]|url=https://www.smcaen.fr/2021-2022/actualites/groupe-pro/ali-abdi-nouveau-joueur-du-stade-malherbe-caen|title=ALI ABDI NOUVEAU JOUEUR DU STADE MALHERBE CAEN|date=21 July 2021|language=fr}}</ref>

On 2 September 2024, Abdi signed for [[Ligue 1]] club [[OGC Nice|Nice]] for a fee of €500,000.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-02 |title=Caen : Ali Abdi s'engage à Nice (off) |url=https://www.foot-national.com/ligue-2/caen-ali-abdi-s-engage-a-nice-off-886214 |access-date=2024-09-03 |website=Foot National |language=fr}}</ref> This transfer was completed outside the regular transfer window dates thanks to a "joker" transfer exemption granted by the [[Ligue de Football Professionnel]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-03 |title=Official {{!}} Ali Abdi completes OGC Nice following Jordan Lotomba exit |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/official-ali-abdi-completes-ogc-070400322.html#:~:text=Tunisia%20international%20Ali%20Abdi%20(30,on%20a%20%E2%80%9Cjoker%E2%80%9D%20transfer. |access-date=2024-09-03 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref>

==International career==
Abdi made his debut for the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]] on 25 March 2021 in an [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group J|AFCON 2021 qualifier]] against [[Libya national football team|Libya]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Eurosport]]|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/africa-cup-of-nations-qualification/2021/live-libya-tunisia_mtc1162691/live.shtml|title=Libya v Tunisia game report|date=25 March 2021}}</ref>

